comment: * Constants and helper functions for use with {@link Os}.

variables.name: EXDEV
variables.comment: On Linux, EWOULDBLOCK == EAGAIN. Use EAGAIN instead, to reduce confusion.

variables.name: NETLINK_INET_DIAG
variables.comment: * SELinux enforces that only system_server and netd may use this netlink socket type.

variables.name: SOCK_CLOEXEC
variables.comment:
* Set the close-on-exec ({@code FD_CLOEXEC}) flag on the new file * descriptor created by {@link Os#socket(int,int,int)} or * {@link Os#socketpair(int,int,int,java.io.FileDescriptor,java.io.FileDescriptor)}. * See the description of the O_CLOEXEC flag in * open(2) * for reasons why this may be useful. * *

Applications wishing to make use of this flag on older API versions * may use {@link #O_CLOEXEC} instead. On Android, {@code O_CLOEXEC} and * {@code SOCK_CLOEXEC} are the same value.

variables.name: SOCK_NONBLOCK
variables.comment:
* Set the O_NONBLOCK file status flag on the file descriptor * created by {@link Os#socket(int,int,int)} or * {@link Os#socketpair(int,int,int,java.io.FileDescriptor,java.io.FileDescriptor)}. * *

Applications wishing to make use of this flag on older API versions * may use {@link #O_NONBLOCK} instead. On Android, {@code O_NONBLOCK} * and {@code SOCK_NONBLOCK} are the same value.

methods.name: public static int CAP_TO_INDEX(int x)
methods.comment:
* Returns the index of the element in the cap_user_data array that this capability is stored
     * in.
     * @hide

methods.name: public static int CAP_TO_MASK(int x)
methods.comment:
* Returns the mask for the given capability. This is relative to the capability's cap_user_data
     * element, the index of which can be retrieved with CAP_TO_INDEX.
     * @hide

methods.name: public static boolean S_ISBLK(int mode)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the given mode is a block device.

methods.name: public static boolean S_ISCHR(int mode)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the given mode is a character device.

methods.name: public static boolean S_ISDIR(int mode)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the given mode is a directory.

methods.name: public static boolean S_ISFIFO(int mode)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the given mode is a FIFO.

methods.name: public static boolean S_ISREG(int mode)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the given mode is a regular file.

methods.name: public static boolean S_ISLNK(int mode)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the given mode is a symbolic link.

methods.name: public static boolean S_ISSOCK(int mode)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the given mode is a socket.

methods.name: public static int WEXITSTATUS(int status)
methods.comment: * Extracts the exit status of a child. Only valid if WIFEXITED returns true.

methods.name: public static boolean WCOREDUMP(int status)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the child dumped core. Only valid if WIFSIGNALED returns true.

methods.name: public static int WTERMSIG(int status)
methods.comment: * Returns the signal that caused the child to exit. Only valid if WIFSIGNALED returns true.

methods.name: public static int WSTOPSIG(int status)
methods.comment: * Returns the signal that cause the child to stop. Only valid if WIFSTOPPED returns true.

methods.name: public static boolean WIFEXITED(int status)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the child exited normally.

methods.name: public static boolean WIFSTOPPED(int status)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the child was stopped (not terminated) by a signal.

methods.name: public static boolean WIFSIGNALED(int status)
methods.comment: * Tests whether the child was terminated by a signal.

methods.name: public static String gaiName(int error)
methods.comment:
* Returns the string name of a getaddrinfo(3) error value.
     * For example, "EAI_AGAIN".

methods.name: public static String errnoName(int errno)
methods.comment:
* Returns the string name of an errno value.
     * For example, "EACCES". See {@link Os#strerror} for human-readable errno descriptions.

methods.name: private static int placeholder()
methods.comment: A hack to avoid these constants being inlined by javac...
